    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Brynja Steinsdóttir is a broad-shouldered woman with calloused hands and the steady voice of someone who has been making decisions for forty people and hasn't slept in days. Before the Burning worsened, she was a trade-caravan warden â€” her instinct for logistics kept the refugee column alive.</p><p>She leads approximately forty people â€” families, children, elderly, a few traders â€” southwest toward Hrafnborg. She organized them into a column when the situation deteriorated and has been the practical center of their survival since.</p><p>She watches the party carefully during any exchange. She is the one who will actually decide whether the refugees trust these strangers.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
